comments.text:
This has got to be your best episode. The constant changes of perspective reflects the techniques you see in good films. I also think this episode feels a bit different...
For example:
1. Knuckles and Sonia are officially in a relationship.
2. Flora has feelings for Sonia (I wonder if things will get spicy later and some drama arises).
3. Mark didn't get emotional at the psuedo cripple man, he stood his ground as a true man.
4. You brought up prior episodes when Sonia and Sonic were arguing.
5. Bartleby wasn't necessarily in the spotlight, and his sub plot still mattered. He made Sonic's day.
6. Also... Sleet and Dingo are by themselves now. They're poor, but they're happy together it seems like...(Sleet was a bit envious of Robotnik's riches, but I'm sure he and Dingo will maybe find better jobs). Especially the fact they're 13k in debt.
Anyways....

Best episode in terms of plot and character progression.
Thank you, Tamers.
